Culture.name: {=XM9EPZDi}Saikai
Culture.text: {=60nJZSa2}SaikaidÅ, meaning 'West Sea Circuit', is the westernmost region of Japan, comprising the island of Kyushu. Far from the power struggles for control of the shogunate in the capital and closer to the Asian mainland, the region has grown into a maritime and trade center, with goods and new ideas being brought by Chinese and Korean traders and most recently by newly come nanban foreigners. Although the Saikai people have a long tradition of sea commerce with other countries, they are no strangers to warfare either, as daimyo battle for control of the islands while swarms of pirates harass the profitable trade routes for plunder.
